parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops or loses power
the vehicle rolls backwards while in park
the transmission fails to engage or disengage
the vehicle is unable to move in any gear
the key can be removed from the ignition while the car is in drive
and the car starts to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty seat belt buckle can lead to accidents or injuries, as it may not provide adequate protection in the event of a crash, or even trap occupants, including children, in their car seats.
symptoms: the seat belt will not open
the seat belt is difficult to release
are trapped in their car seats.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Lighting System Failure due to Electrical Short
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear lighting system can cause a loss of visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions. In severe cases, an electrical short can lead to a fire, posing a risk to the vehicle's occupants and other road users.
symptoms: tail lights are dim or flickering
burning smell or smoke from the rear of the vehicle
visible signs of electrical arcing or burning.
